cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with relocalization of camera pose using event images. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the application of the proposed method in robotics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper uses a Stacked Spatial LSTM Network for learning spatial dependencies in the image feature space. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper deals with a task related to perception and localization, which are important areas in AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses a neural network architecture for learning.
